Change Shape (Su)			KEY:Change Shape ~ Forest Dragon	SOURCEPAGE:p.94	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RaceAbility.SpecialQuality	DESC:An adult or older forest dragon can assume any humanoid form three times per day as if using polymorph.
Destructive Crush (Su)		KEY:Destructive Crush ~ Forest Dragon	SOURCEPAGE:p.94	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RaceAbility.SpecialQuality	DESC:When an old or older forest dragon makes a crush attack, the impact kicks up debris in a 20-foot-radius burst for 1d6 rounds. The debris obscures the vision of creatures within the debris field and grants concealment to those creatures. The forest dragon can see normally within and through the debris field.
Elemental Breath (Su)		KEY:Elemental Breath ~ Forest Dragon	SOURCEPAGE:p.94	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RaceAbility.SpecialQuality	DESC:Once per day, when an ancient or older forest dragon uses its breath weapon, it can summon a greater earth elemental within the cone. The caster level for these effects is the same as the dragon's caster level.
Sound Imitation (Ex)		KEY:Sound Imitation ~ Forest Dragon	SOURCEPAGE:p.94	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RaceAbility.SpecialQuality	DESC:A very young or older forest dragon can mimic any voice or sound it has heard by making a successful Bluff check against the listener's Sense Motive check.
Stony Death (Su)			KEY:Stony Death ~ Forest Dragon	SOURCEPAGE:p.94	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RaceAbility.SpecialQuality	DESC:Any creature reduced to 0 or fewer hit points by a great wyrm forest dragon's breath weapon must also make a Fortitude save (same DC as the forest dragon's breath weapon) or be petrified as the flesh to stone spell. This is a death effect.
Woodland Stride (Ex)		KEY:Woodland Stride ~ Forest Dragon	SOURCEPAGE:p.94	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:RaceAbility.SpecialQuality	DESC:As the druid ability of the same name.
